    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Cut a few rounds off your<strong> red chilli[s] </strong>(set them aside for garnish), then cut the <strong>remaining red chilli </strong>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hoisin-mushrooms-with-sesame-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crumble in your <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until they're starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hoisin-mushrooms-with-sesame-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, add your <strong>wholewheat noodles</strong> to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until they're fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-7 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and set aside in a bowl and reserve the pot for later</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hoisin-mushrooms-with-sesame-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong> then pat them dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hoisin-mushrooms-with-sesame-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have softened, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>to the pan</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min further or until the mushrooms are coated in a sticky sauce \u2013 these are your <strong>hoisin mushrooms</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hoisin-mushrooms-with-sesame-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> shredded kale</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1 min or until starting to wilt</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hoisin-mushrooms-with-sesame-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a splash of<strong> water</strong> and cook, covered, for 2 min or until completely wilted, then stir in the <strong>drained noodles </strong>and<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>sesame noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hoisin-mushrooms-with-sesame-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>hoisin mushrooms</strong> over the<strong> sesame noodles</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
